The paper deals with knowledge graph embedding, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that involves representing symbolic entities and relations in continuous vector spaces. The paper also uses a Transformer encoder, which is a popular deep learning architecture for natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on various benchmarks, which is a common practice in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with graph contexts and path query answering, which are topics in databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
